In this press briefing, Press Secretary Jay Carney discusses various topics including Edward Snowden's request for asylum in Russia, the President's meeting with the Attorney General and the release of the DOJ report on media relations and investigations, the departure of Secretary Napolitano, the use of the nuclear option in the Senate, the decision on post-2014 troop levels in Afghanistan, the Trayvon Martin case, the farm bill, the Edward Snowden case, the Winter Olympics in Russia, the LGBT workplace nondiscrimination executive order, the forced feeding of detainees in Guantanamo, and assistance to the rebels in Syria.